

1. Help me look around corners
"Act as my personal news aggregator. I am a [insert your level/role] in the [insert function] at a [insert company size and industry] company. List the top 5 emerging trends, disruptions, or news items I need to know this week to show up as a credible expert. For each item, briefly explain why it matters to my specific role and how I can weave it into leadership conversations."

2. Radiate my brand
"I am writing an email to [insert stakeholder, e.g., a senior executive, a cross-functional team]. My goal for this message is to [insert goal]. Here is my current draft: [insert draft]. Please rewrite this message so that it sounds [insert 2-3 tone adjectives, e.g., confident, concise, and collaborative]. Ensure the revised version strongly reflects my personal brand as an expert in [insert your expertise]."

3. Help me live my brand
"Translate my core leadership values into observable actions. I want to be known for [insert 3-4 traits, e.g., warmth, passion for growth, urgency, and a bias toward action]. I am an expert in [insert expertise]. What exactly would these values look like in my day-to-day behavior? Provide 5 highly specific examples of how I should show up in meetings tomorrow, how I should structure my emails, and how I should prioritize my tasks to reflect this brand."

4. Connect with the best
"I want to strategically expand my network in the [insert industry/field] space. First, suggest 3-4 types of thought leaders, roles, or organizations I should follow or connect with. Second, draft a short, compelling LinkedIn outreach note I can use to connect with a senior leader in this space, highlighting my interest in [insert specific topic]. Finally, provide 3 insightful questions I can ask them during a 15-minute introductory coffee chat."

5. Cliff notes for my sponsor
"Below is the text from my recent performance review (Note: I have removed all confidential company data). Based on this feedback, what are the top 3 key messages a sponsor should use to advocate for my promotion or next opportunity? What specific evidence from the text suggests I am ready for broader leadership? Finally, summarize the 'leadership brand' that emerges from this review in two concise sentences. [Insert scrubbed performance review text]"

6. Roleplay with me
"Act as a [insert title of senior leader, e.g., VP of Marketing] who is outside of my core function. I am a [insert your role] and I have scheduled a 20-minute meeting with you to ask for your mentorship/sponsorship. Let's roleplay this conversation. Start the simulation by greeting me and asking why I wanted to meet. Ask me questions one by one, wait for my response, and push back or raise objections as a busy executive might. After our roleplay is over, provide critical feedback on how I handled the 'ask'."
  
